CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 10, 1965, pg. 6 reads: "Benefit Tea - Members of the Elite Social and Charitable Club recently sponsored a beautiful Rose Tea at the Centre Avenue YMCA. Proceeds were for the benefit of the Harriet Tubman Guild's Building Fund.  A highlight of the tea was the presentation of $200 to Mrs. Georgia Quash, president of the Guild, who was guest speaker.  Officers and members of the sponsoring organization are (left to right) Mrs. Ann Jackson, financial secretary; Mrs. Lucille Harris, treasurer; Mrs. Selina Sheffey, chaplain; Mrs. Janie Stewart, recording secretary; Mrs. Jonella Jeffrey, assistant treasurer; Mrs. Quash, accepting check; Mrs. Nellie M. McKinney, Mrs. Georgia Brown Turner, club president; Mrs. Margaret Avery, club reporter, and Mrs. Addie Chandler, co-chairman of the tea.  Mrs. Alice Brooks, chairman; Mmes. Manzella Lane nad Louise McPherson were absent.- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Ten women, members of the Elite Social and Charitable Club, left to right: Ann Jackson, Lucille Harris, Selina Sheffey, Janie Stewart, Jonella Jeffrey, Georgia Quash accepting check, Nellie M. McKinney, Georgia Brown Turner, Margaret Avery, and Addie Chandler, standing behind banquet table with punch bowls and flower arrangements, Centre Avenue YMCA
